This shows the key accumulation logic for unshown/reconnection scenarios. Lines 136-138 show the loop that accumulates wins:

```typescript
// 計算上一輪累積贏分
for (let i = 0; i < this.m_startRound; i++) {
    this.m_previousAccumulatedWinValue += this.m_unshowSpinAckQue[i].RoundWin;
}
```

This explicitly sums up RoundWin from multiple rounds in the unshown queue. The comment says "計算上一輪累積贏分" (Calculate previous round accumulated wins).

So for reconnection/unshow scenarios, the system explicitly accumulates wins from multiple RoundInfo instances. But the question is whether NORMAL gameplay (non-reconnection) with multiple RoundInfo also displays accumulated wins correctly.

